  "text": "Data We use the WORLD dataset [CITATION_1] , which covers 3,709 cities worldwide and consists of tweets from 1.4M users. [CITATION_2] hold out 10,000 users as development and 10,000 as test set. For each user with at least 10 geotagged tweets, the user's location is set to be the city in which the majority of their tweets are from. We also use [CITATION_3] 's method to extract the nearest city to a given latitudelongitude coordinate.",
